**Defense in Depth Layers**:

1. **Session ID Regeneration on Authentication**:
```java
// Old session destroyed, new session created on login
public String regenerateSessionOnLogin(String oldSessionId, String username, ...) {
    if (oldSessionId != null) {
        invalidateSession(oldSessionId);  // Destroy pre-auth session
    }
    String newSessionId = generateSecureSessionId();  // Fresh ID
    // ... create new authenticated session
}
```

2. **Dual Timeout Protection**:
```java
// Idle timeout - expires after inactivity
long idleTime = Instant.now().toEpochMilli() - session.getLastAccessedAt();
if (idleTime > SESSION_TIMEOUT.toMillis()) { /* invalidate */ }

// Absolute timeout - maximum session lifetime regardless of activity
long sessionAge = Instant.now().toEpochMilli() - session.getCreatedAt();
if (sessionAge > ABSOLUTE_TIMEOUT.toMillis()) { /* invalidate */ }
```

3. **Client Binding Validation**:
```java
// Detect session theft via IP/User-Agent changes
if (!session.getClientIp().equals(currentIp)) {
    logger.warning("SECURITY: Session IP changed...");
    // Alert security team, optionally invalidate
}
```

**Additional Protections**:

- **Secure Cookie Flags**: HttpOnly prevents XSS session theft; Secure ensures HTTPS-only transmission; SameSite=Strict blocks CSRF attacks
- **Centralized Session Store**: Redis enables session sharing across load-balanced servers with automatic TTL expiration
- **CSRF Token Generation**: Each session includes bound CSRF token for form/API protection
- **Comprehensive Audit Logging**: All session lifecycle events logged without exposing sensitive session IDs
- **Sliding Window Expiration**: Session TTL refreshed on each valid request, but absolute timeout prevents indefinite sessions
- **Graceful Degradation**: Redis failures handled safely, preventing authentication bypass during outages
